The paper deals with the assessment of human behavior in video-based structured interviews, which involves aspects of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on biases in human annotations also suggests a potential connection to fairness and accountability in machine learning (cs.FA). However, since the paper does not explicitly discuss these topics, cs.FA is less likely to be a relevant sub-category.
